Since its first showcase years ago, Marvel’s Spider-Man has been one of Sony’s biggest games to hang the PlayStation 4’s hat on. Now, we’re getting a new look at its gameplay thanks to a new trailer. Spidey is shown kicking enemies, webbing others up, riding a helicopter to help prevent it from crashing, and swinging through various parts of the city before battling Scorpion and then Rhino.

summary: What if the majority of the adults (and anyone that pays attention) in Queens and Midtown School of Science and Technology knows...
body: What if the majority of the adults (and anyone that pays attention) in Queens and Midtown School of Science and Technology knows that Peter Parker is Spider-Man? All the teachers know. Mr. Harrington knows and anytime Peter he shows up for a meet he is just thankful Peter is alive. Mr. Del Mar knows. Principal Morita definitely knows. He has conference calls with Tony and May and promises to keep an eye out on him and not let him know that they know because it keeps him somewhat under wraps because if Spidey had no barriers it would be impossible to keep him inside. There are cameras everywhere in New York City. Somewhere there is an NYPD officer like “Hey. Parker got another churro from that nice lady.”

body:
Peter Parker as a teacher


I’d love to see Peter become a teacher again. I feel like that’s his true calling. I didn’t used to think so but after reading the entirety of the Spectacular Spider-Man run of the comics the build-up is actually pretty clear. When he was a T.A. In college teaching classes he just fit right in. He showed he had the right kind of stuff to inspire his students and to take all their problems in stride. Horizon Lavs was an interesting choice for Peter and when you look at his story as a summary taking out certain important bits of characterization it even seems like the most logical choice but when you consider the fine details, the subtle character development Peter becoming a science teacher actually makes more sense narratively. I think thatwas the true difference between Straczynski and Slott.

Peter, after getting stabbed multiple times and being crushed by a building twice: o heck i forgot about that spanish test tomorrow

Peter, after dropping his hotdog: you know, life really doesn’t have any meaning, does it? What am i doing here protecting the lives of people that will die eventually anyways? There’s no true meaning to why life was created in the first place. We were all just born to die. Why try to live when we know our inevitable end
